      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "People Dealing With Persistent Acne",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Blue light therapy is one of the few non-pharmaceutical interventions with solid clinical evidence for acne. If you have tried topicals and oral treatments with mixed results, adding LED therapy can be the missing piece.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Anyone Over 30 Starting to Notice Fine Lines",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Collagen production drops roughly one percent per year after your mid-twenties. Red and near-infrared light therapy stimulates fibroblasts to produce more collagen. Starting early means maintaining what you have; starting later means rebuilding what you lost. Both work.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
